Package: rcicrely
Title: Toolkit for Reliability Analysis of Classification Images from Reverse Correlation Studies in Social Psychology
Version: 0.2.2
Authors@R:
    person("Manuel", "Oliveira",
           email = "manuel.olivethree@gmail.com",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Assess the reliability of classification images (CIs) produced
    by reverse-correlation experiments. Covers within-condition consistency
    (permuted split-half with Spearman-Brown correction, leave-one-out
    sensitivity, ICC(3,1) and ICC(3,k) via direct mean-squares) and
    between-condition discriminability (pixel-wise Welch t, cluster-based
    permutation with max-statistic family-wise error control, bootstrap
    representational dissimilarity). Supports both standard 2IFC (via the
    upstream rcicr package) and Brief-RC 12 (Schmitz, Rougier & Yzerbyt,
    2024 — implemented natively in this package). Operates directly on the
    pixel-level signal produced by the original producers, so it does not
    depend on a second-phase trait-rating study.
